<h2 id="our-guarantee">Our Guarantee</h2>

<p>We stand behind our work with a straightforward guarantee: <strong>if our audit does not identify at least 10 actionable issues that you were not already aware of, we will refund your payment in full.</strong></p>

<p>We have never had to honour this guarantee. In five years of auditing websites, we have never encountered a site — regardless of how well-maintained it appeared — that did not have at least 15 to 20 previously undetected issues. Most sites have 30 to 50.</p>

<p>We also guarantee delivery within 7 business days for Basic and Comprehensive audits, or 14 business days for Enterprise. If we miss the deadline, you receive a 20 percent discount.</p>

<p>There is no risk. If the audit does not deliver value, you do not pay. That is how confident we are in the depth and quality of our work.</p>

<h2 id="faq">FAQ</h2>

<h3>How long does the audit take?</h3>
<p>Basic audits are delivered within 5 business days. Comprehensive audits within 7 business days. Enterprise audits within 14 business days. These are maximum timelines — most audits are delivered 1-2 days early.</p>

<h3>What access do you need?</h3>
<p>Read-only access to Google Search Console is required. Read-only access to Google Analytics is optional but recommended as it allows us to correlate SEO issues with conversion data. We never need CMS access, hosting credentials, or write access to anything.</p>

<h3>Will you implement the fixes?</h3>
<p>The audit service covers analysis and recommendations only. We provide implementation instructions detailed enough for any competent developer or marketer to follow. If you want us to implement the fixes, we offer that as a separate engagement at pre-agreed rates, typically at a discount for audit clients.</p>

<h3>How is this different from a free audit tool?</h3>
<p>Free audit tools run automated checks and flag surface-level issues. They cannot interpret context, identify root causes, evaluate content quality, assess competitive positioning, or write strategy-level recommendations. Our audit combines automated data with senior human analysis. The output is a strategic document, not a list of tool warnings. Read our comparison of <a href="/website-audit-tools/best-free/">free audit tools</a> to understand what they can and cannot do.</p>

<h3>Do you work with agencies?</h3>
<p>Yes. We offer <a href="/website-audit-services/agencies/">white-label audit services for agencies</a> at volume discounts. The report is delivered under your brand with your formatting. Your clients never know we were involved.</p>

<h3>What if my site is very large or technically complex?</h3>
<p>Sites with over 50,000 pages, JavaScript-rendered content, multi-language configurations, or complex e-commerce architectures require our Enterprise tier with custom scoping. Contact us with your site URL and we will provide a custom quote within 24 hours.</p>

<h3>Can I see a sample report first?</h3>
<p>Absolutely. <a href="/website-audit-services/report-example/">View our sample audit report</a> to see exactly what you will receive. The sample is from a real audit (with client details anonymised) and represents the quality and depth of every report we produce.</p>

